00:39:25,029 --> 00:39:31,636
Hello, uh, thank you for starting us off so strong. Two questions, one, um, how do you guys

815
00:39:31,896 --> 00:39:37,622
go about, uh, when you're early on in a project and you have the fortune to be actually on a

816
00:39:37,662 --> 00:39:42,567
project early in a narrative capacity and they're still settling a lot of the gameplay stuff.

817
00:39:43,448 --> 00:39:48,012
How much, there's some questions about how much setting work you do versus how much story work you do.

818
00:39:49,013 --> 00:39:55,098
Like, literally, if you're still doing prototype work, and you don't even know exactly what the game's going to be,

819
00:39:55,518 --> 00:40:00,543
but you're still working on the sides, like, how far do you think it's good to go with setting stuff?

820
00:40:01,263 --> 00:40:05,187
The other question I have is, have you ever been to the Golden Gate Tap Room?

821
00:40:06,037 --> 00:40:10,341
you know why i have a very good plan that doesn't look like a tap room is a

