00:40:21,485 --> 00:40:22,746
In terms of establishing setting,

827
00:40:22,826 --> 00:40:24,708
if you happen to be on a project very early,

828
00:40:24,728 --> 00:40:27,130
you normally have quite a small team, which I enjoy.

829
00:40:27,570 --> 00:40:29,772
And for me, the way that I go about creating the setting

830
00:40:29,812 --> 00:40:31,813
is I go and I talk to each of the people on the team

831
00:40:31,873 --> 00:40:34,235
about what is important for them in this game.

832
00:40:34,715 --> 00:40:35,896
So what do they wanna say?

833
00:40:35,976 --> 00:40:37,097
What do they wanna experience?

834
00:40:37,137 --> 00:40:38,618
What do they want the player to experience?

835
00:40:38,759 --> 00:40:40,760
And then I look at all of those and see where they connect.

836
00:40:41,421 --> 00:40:42,581
And that's where I start with setting.

837
00:40:45,451 --> 00:40:50,435
So most of the projects I've worked on have been in established settings. So like

