00:43:04,543 --> 00:43:11,089
going to be on the systems designers to make sure that that is communicated properly. But if

872
00:43:11,129 --> 00:43:16,793
players are going to be skipping dialogue, then there's not a lot you can do about it except to

873
00:43:16,874 --> 00:43:22,238
try to build in proper tutorialization just throughout the game. So as to reinforce these

874
00:43:22,318 --> 00:43:23,159
points that you're trying to hit.

875
00:43:23,805 --> 00:43:28,227
The other thing that you can do if you're playing a game that has a journal is you can lean on the journal.

876
00:43:28,287 --> 00:43:28,987
We do that a lot.

877
00:43:29,367 --> 00:43:34,609
So if players, if you put something important in a dialogue, always make sure it's in the journal too.

878
00:43:34,629 --> 00:43:38,271
Because even if you've got a player who's reading through everything carefully,

879
00:43:38,411 --> 00:43:40,772
something could happen, the cat jumps on the keyboard, whatever it is,

880
00:43:40,812 --> 00:43:43,473
and they somehow miss whatever that critical line is.

881
00:43:43,933 --> 00:43:46,935
So lean on the journal so the player can always go back to the critical stuff.

882
00:43:47,954 --> 00:43:49,975
After watching numerous Let's Plays of my games

883
00:43:50,035 --> 00:43:51,595
and seeing people skip through everything,

884
00:43:52,075 --> 00:43:54,155
I realized that the gameplay choice that you should support.

885
00:43:55,316 --> 00:43:57,436
And also I find tutorials very offensive.

