00:44:59,320 --> 00:45:04,523
missing out? And like players who would just create save files after save files after save files

908
00:45:04,564 --> 00:45:05,264
to see everything.

909
00:45:06,572 --> 00:45:07,752
Players are very smart.

910
00:45:08,012 --> 00:45:09,273
They're going to realize pretty quickly

911
00:45:09,313 --> 00:45:11,114
if their choices don't mean anything.

912
00:45:11,694 --> 00:45:13,315
So knowing what endings you can have

913
00:45:13,355 --> 00:45:15,275
that are actually going to affect something later

914
00:45:15,315 --> 00:45:16,956
in the game is the starting point for me.

915
00:45:16,996 --> 00:45:18,137
I need to know where I'm going

916
00:45:18,177 --> 00:45:19,797
so that I can take the player on a journey

917
00:45:20,157 --> 00:45:21,798
rather than designing from the beginning

918
00:45:21,838 --> 00:45:23,199
and going, oh, that would be so cool.

919
00:45:23,639 --> 00:45:25,120
Wait, I can't do it, and neither can the player.

920
00:45:27,141 --> 00:45:32,343
Two things. One is try to be strategic about the choices that you offer to players.

921
00:45:32,564 --> 00:45:37,286
So make sure that the choices you do offer have a lot of reactivity.

922
00:45:37,646 --> 00:45:41,708
So if that means, like, based on your budget, if that means you can only afford to do, like,

923
00:45:41,829 --> 00:45:46,331
four big choices in the game, figure out what those four choices are, but pay the heck off on them.

924
00:45:46,371 --> 00:45:48,572
Like, really pay off as much as you possibly can.

925
00:45:48,592 --> 00:45:51,734
Have a lot of things that react to whatever each of those choices is.

926
00:45:52,594 --> 00:45:57,298
The other thing is make sure as players are playing through your game, draw attention to the fact that,

927
00:45:57,738 --> 00:46:02,841
oh, this was, this is happening because you made that choice. Like literally you can say in a dialogue,

928
00:46:03,182 --> 00:46:07,204
well, because you killed that guy, now I'm after you, right? Whatever it is, like draw attention to that,

929
00:46:07,244 --> 00:46:11,067
because a lot of times players won't even realize that they've had a choice that they've made

930
00:46:11,367 --> 00:46:16,111
that actually has a big impact on the game, unless you're drawing attention to it multiple times.

931
00:46:16,291 --> 00:46:20,153
And that's more likely to get them to come back and play through it again and see your different choices.

932
00:46:20,579 --> 00:46:21,660
There's three things you can do.

933
00:46:21,861 --> 00:46:23,503
Usually a narrative, even if it branches,

934
00:46:23,543 --> 00:46:25,305
always comes back to a certain choke point.

935
00:46:25,325 --> 00:46:26,947
And you don't want to do that too frequently,

936
00:46:27,267 --> 00:46:29,470
but use those choke points to your advantage.

937
00:46:29,530 --> 00:46:31,652
Like that's the moment you can use all the reactivity

938
00:46:31,672 --> 00:46:34,075
that George is describing in a very efficient way.

939
00:46:34,095 --> 00:46:35,958
Two other things you can do is one is,

940
00:46:36,018 --> 00:46:38,621
if you can ever have the reactivity be systemic,

941
00:46:39,081 --> 00:46:41,144
but still narrative involved.

